The paper discusses security implications of using pre-trained models in machine learning systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on deep learning systems, which suggests that it could also fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses potential countermeasures and challenges in implementing them, which could also relate to software engineering (cs.SE).
